    public class ApplicationWindow
extends javax.swing.JFrame
    The ApplicationWindow class represents the main graphical user interface that the CSR uses to interact with the application. It is instantiated in the actionPerformed method of the OK button listener for whichever configuration dialog was launched (i.e. client or standalone). The JFrame itself contains UI elements such as a JTable to list all the available subcontractors and also provides other fields to search and book records as per the application requirements. Because it is known which mode we are executing in when we create this class we are able to "inject" the relevant business component as a constructor argument. The interaction with the business service component is then implemented in the action listeners of the UI components i.e. Book button, Search button etc.
    Author:
    Kieran O'Brien
